ITALY DAYBOOK: Matteo Arpe May Join Popolare Milano’s Board

-- B y   T o m m a s o   E b h a r d t
-- 
2011-10-11T05:09:22Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-10-11/italy-daybook-matteo-arpe-may-join-popolare-milano-s-board.html
Former Capitalia SpA Chief Executive
Officer Matteo Arpe may join  Banca Popolare di Milano Scrl ’s
management board, said Marcello Messori, a candidate to become
chairman of the bank.  Italy ’s Treasury aims to sell a total of 9.5 billion euros
in bills in bond sales today.  The country’s public debt surged more than twice as much
under  Silvio Berlusconi  than under his rival premiers since the
media tycoon entered politics 17 years ago.  The Bloomberg CHART OF THE DAY shows that Berlusconi has
overseen a 13.5 percent cumulative increase in debt per capita
while in office.  EQUITIES:
* Italcementi SpA (IT)   holds a presentation at Bank of America
Merrill Lynch Pan European Building & Infrastructure Conference
in London AT 10:45 a.m.
* Edison SpA (EDN)   sold Taranto Energia Srl, which owns two
thermoelectric plants, to Ilva for about 164.4 million euros
 * CIR SpA (CIR)   Carlo De Benedetti, the Italian entrepreneur
who controls the  investment company , will sign an agreement with
Milan’s Bocconi University at 3 p.m.  GOVERNMENT:
*Labor Minister  Maurizio Sacconi , Democratic Party Deputy
Secretary  Enrico Letta attend  the presentation of a report on
citizenship and economy in Italy organized by the think-tank
Farefuturo in  Rome .
*Giuseppe Mussari, head of Italy’s banking association, speaks
at the Senate’s Finance Committee at 3 p.m.  MARKETS:
*The benchmark  FTSE MIB Index (FTSEMIB)  rose for a fourth day, adding 3.67
percent to 16,098.16.
*The  yield spread  on 10-year Italian bonds and similar German
securities narrowed 3.1 basis points to 348.8275 basis points.  To contact the reporter on this story:
